    :target: https://python-chess.readthedocs.io/en/v0.27.3/

Introduction
------------

python-chess is a pure Python chess library with move generation, move
validation and support for common formats. This is the Scholar's mate in
python-chess:

.. code:: python

    >>> import chess

    >>> board = chess.Board()

    >>> board.legal_moves
    <LegalMoveGenerator at ... (Nh3, Nf3, Nc3, Na3, h3, g3, f3, e3, d3, c3, ...)>
    >>> chess.Move.from_uci("a8a1") in board.legal_moves
    False

    >>> board.push_san("e4")
    Move.from_uci('e2e4')
    >>> board.push_san("e5")
    Move.from_uci('e7e5')
    >>> board.push_san("Qh5")
    Move.from_uci('d1h5')
    >>> board.push_san("Nc6")
    Move.from_uci('b8c6')
    >>> board.push_san("Bc4")
    Move.from_uci('f1c4')
    >>> board.push_san("Nf6")
    Move.from_uci('g8f6')
    >>> board.push_san("Qxf7")
    Move.from_uci('h5f7')

    >>> board.is_checkmate()
    True

    >>> board
    Board('r1bqkb1r/pppp1Qpp/2n2n2/4p3/2B1P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNB1K1NR b KQkq - 0 4')

